Parameter examples¶

Mostly modeled on Vega-Lite documentation.

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import altair as alt
from vega_datasets import data

cornerRadius¶

df = pd.DataFrame([
      {"a": "A", "b": 28}, {"a": "B", "b": 55}, {"a": "C", "b": 43},
      {"a": "D", "b": 91}, {"a": "E", "b": 81}, {"a": "F", "b": 53},
      {"a": "G", "b": 19}, {"a": "H", "b": 87}, {"a": "I", "b": 52}
    ])

rad_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=20, step=1)
rad_var = alt.parameter(bind=rad_slider, value=0, name="cornerRadius")

c = alt.Chart(df).mark_bar(cornerRadius=rad_var).encode(
    x='a:N',
    y='b:Q',
).add_parameter(rad_var)

c

Variables in terms of other variables¶

df = pd.DataFrame({"r1":[310,0],"r2":[270,0],"r3":[125,225]})

height_slider = alt.binding_range(min=1, max=100, step=1)
height_var = alt.parameter(bind=height_slider, value=20, name="height")

inner_var = height_var/2
tick_var = 3*height_var/4

c1 = alt.Chart().mark_bar(
    color="#eee",
    size = height_var
).encode(
    x = "r1"
)

c2 = alt.Chart().mark_bar(
    color="steelblue",
    size = inner_var
).encode(
    x = "r2"
)

c3 = alt.Chart().mark_tick(
    color="black",
    size = tick_var,
    thickness=2
).encode(
    x = "r3"
)

alt.LayerChart(df, layer=[c1,c2,c3]).encode(
    x = alt.X(title=None)
).add_parameter(height_var, inner_var, tick_var)

size and opacity¶

cars = data.cars.url

year_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=1000, step=5)
size_var = alt.parameter(bind=year_slider, value=200)

c = alt.Chart(cars).mark_circle(size=size_var+100+100, opacity=size_var/1000).encode(
    x='Miles_per_Gallon:Q',
    y='Horsepower:Q',
).add_parameter(size_var)

c

cutoff¶

rand = np.random.RandomState(42)

df = pd.DataFrame({
    'xval': range(100),
    'yval': rand.randn(100).cumsum()
})

slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=100, step=1)
cutoff = alt.parameter(bind=slider, value = 50)

alt.Chart(df).mark_point().encode(
    x='xval',
    y='yval',
    color=alt.condition(
        alt.datum.xval < cutoff,
        alt.value('red'), alt.value('blue')
    )
).add_parameter(
    cutoff
)

layer chart¶

cars = data.cars.url

slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=240, step=1)
ypos = alt.parameter(bind=slider, value = 100)

dots= alt.Chart(cars).mark_circle().encode(
    x='Miles_per_Gallon:Q',
    y='Horsepower:Q',
    color=alt.condition(
            alt.datum.Horsepower > ypos,
            alt.value('red'), alt.value('blue')
        )
)

yrule = alt.Chart().mark_rule().encode(
        y=alt.datum(ypos, type="quantitative")
)

(dots + yrule).add_parameter(ypos)

Selection point¶

cars = data.cars()

brush = alt.selection_point()

alt.Chart(cars).mark_rect().encode(
    x = "Cylinders:N",
    y = "Origin",
    color = alt.condition(brush,"count()",alt.value("grey")),
).add_parameter(brush).properties(width=240,height=120)

Selection interval¶

cars = data.cars()

brush = alt.selection_interval()

alt.Chart(cars).mark_rect().encode(
    x = "Cylinders:N",
    y = "Origin",
    color = alt.condition(brush,"count()",alt.value("grey")),
).add_parameter(brush).properties(width=240,height=120)

In expression strings¶

In this example, if you click on a point, the size of all points changes according to the y-coordinate of the clicked point.

cars = data.cars()

slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=100)
opacity_var = alt.parameter(bind=slider, value = 50, name="opacityVar")

brush = alt.selection_point(fields = ["Miles_per_Gallon"], toggle = False)

alt.Chart(cars).mark_circle(
    size = brush.Miles_per_Gallon ** 2 | 300,
    opacity=opacity_var/100).encode(
    x = "Horsepower",
    y = "Miles_per_Gallon",
).add_parameter(opacity_var, brush)

As predicate¶

cars = data.cars()

checkbox = alt.binding_checkbox()
origin_var = alt.parameter(bind=checkbox, name="toggleOrigin")

brush = alt.selection(type="point", on="mouseover")

c = alt.Chart(cars).mark_circle().encode(
    x = "Horsepower:Q",
    y = "Miles_per_Gallon:Q",
    color = alt.condition(origin_var,"Origin",alt.value("steelblue")),
    size = alt.condition(brush,alt.value(300),alt.value(25)),
).add_parameter(origin_var, brush)

c

As predicate with empty specified¶

cars = data.cars()

checkbox = alt.binding_checkbox()
origin_var = alt.parameter(bind=checkbox, name="toggleOrigin")

brush = alt.selection(type="point", on="mouseover")

c = alt.Chart(cars).mark_circle().encode(
    x = "Horsepower:Q",
    y = "Miles_per_Gallon:Q",
    color = alt.condition(origin_var,"Origin",alt.value("steelblue")),
    size = alt.condition(brush,alt.value(300),alt.value(50),empty=False),
    opacity = alt.condition(brush,alt.value(1),alt.value(0.4),empty=False),
).add_parameter(origin_var, brush)

c

Filtering data¶

The selection on the top chart filters the data on the bottom chart.

cars = data.cars()

brush = alt.selection_interval()

c1 = alt.Chart().mark_point().encode(
    x = "Horsepower",
    y = "Miles_per_Gallon"
).add_parameter(brush)

c2 = alt.Chart().mark_point().encode(
    x = alt.X("Acceleration", scale=alt.Scale(domain=[0,25])),
    y = alt.Y("Displacement", scale=alt.Scale(domain=[0,500])),
).transform_filter(brush)

alt.VConcatChart(cars, vconcat=(c1,c2))

Binning¶

The selection on the bottom chart determines the extent for the bins on the top chart.

flights = data.flights_5k()

brush = alt.selection_interval(encodings=["x"])

c1 = alt.Chart().mark_bar().encode(
    x = alt.X("time:Q", bin=alt.Bin(maxbins=30,extent=brush)),
    y = "count()"
).properties(
    width = 480,
    height = 150
)

c2 = alt.Chart().mark_bar().encode(
    x = alt.X("time:Q", bin = alt.Bin(maxbins=30)),
    y = alt.Y("count()", axis= alt.Axis(title="Count"))
).add_parameter(brush).properties(
    width = 480,
    height = 50,
)

alt.VConcatChart(data=flights,vconcat=(c1,c2)).transform_calculate(
    time = "hours(datum.date) + minutes(datum.date) / 60"
)

Domain¶

Similar but updating the domain of the top chart.

stocks = data.sp500()

brush = alt.selection_interval(encodings=["x"])

c1 = alt.Chart().mark_area().encode(
    x = alt.X("date:T", scale=alt.Scale(domain=brush), axis=alt.Axis(title="")),
    y = "price:Q"
).properties(
    width = 480,
)

c2 = alt.Chart().mark_area().encode(
    x = "date:T",
    y = alt.Y("price:Q",axis=alt.Axis(tickCount=3, grid=False)),
).add_parameter(brush).properties(width=480,height=60)

alt.VConcatChart(data=stocks,vconcat=(c1,c2))

Many sliders¶

rad_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=100, step=1)
rad_var = alt.parameter(bind=rad_slider, value=0, name="radius")

rad2_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=100, step=1)
rad_var2 = alt.parameter(bind=rad_slider, value=50, name="radius2")

theta_slider = alt.binding_range(min=-2*np.pi, max=2*np.pi)
theta_var = alt.parameter(bind=theta_slider, value=-0.73, name="theta_single_arc")

theta_slider2 = alt.binding_range(min=-2*np.pi, max=2*np.pi)
theta2_var = alt.parameter(bind=theta_slider, value=0.73, name="theta2_single_arc")

corner_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=50, step = 1)
corner_var = alt.parameter(bind=corner_slider, value=0, name="cornerRadius")

pad_slider = alt.binding_range(min=0, max=np.pi/2)
pad_var = alt.parameter(bind=pad_slider, value=0, name="padAngle")

source = pd.DataFrame({"category": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6], "value": [4, 6, 10, 3, 7, 8]})

c1 = alt.Chart().mark_arc(
    radius=rad_var,
    radius2=rad_var2,
    theta = theta_var,
    theta2 = theta2_var,
    cornerRadius = corner_var,
    padAngle = pad_var,
).properties(
    width=200,
    height=200
)

c2 = alt.Chart(source).mark_arc(
    radius=rad_var,
    radius2=rad_var2,
    cornerRadius = corner_var,
    padAngle = pad_var,
).encode(
    theta=alt.Theta(field="value", type="quantitative"),
    color=alt.Color(field="category", type="nominal"),
).properties(
    width=200,
    height=200
)

alt.hconcat(c1,c2).add_parameter(
    rad_var, rad_var2, theta_var, theta2_var, corner_var, pad_var
)

Transform filter¶

Basic form of an example using Vega-Lite API. The slider determines which year the data is taken from.

pop = data.population()

year_slider = alt.binding_range(min=1850, max=2000, step=10)
year_var = alt.parameter(name="Year", bind=year_slider, value=2000)

alt.Chart(pop).mark_bar().encode(
    x = 'sum(people)',
    y = 'age'
).transform_filter(alt.datum.year == year_var).add_parameter(year_var)
